snippet.title: KIDS INDOOR PLAYGROUND |  INDOOR PLAY AREA
snippet.description:
KIDS INDOOR PLAYGROUND | PLAYGROUND FUN PLACE
Kids playing in the indoor playground - This week, we are adding another 2 videos for kids from a trip to the indoor playground with twins.

Our 3 year old children love to watch Blippi videos from indoor playgrounds and other Blippi play place for Kids - so we went out with them to the indoor playground... In the video you will see our  3-year-olds twins playing  with various toys such as  a large ship toy, children's cars, toy houses, toy kitchens, big LEGO brick and large foam colored blocks with different shapes and color. In winter, we often go with our twins to various indoor playgrounds. The kids can go out and run around here. Our boys love to discover all the attractions of the playrooms. Indoor playground provides excellent entertainment for childrens and is a great way to spend time with children, especially on cold and rainy days.

Our kids playing at the indoor playground with big colorful blocks. Every child loves to play with blocks - ours too - but it's even more fun to knock down previously built buildings - the boys did a nice demolition. You can always build something interesting for small children with giant colorful block. Our   Many colors and different shapes make the children interested in playing and stimulate their imagination.In the indoor playground there was a corner with large foam colored blocks in various shapes and colors, so that children can learn to recognize colors and shapes in a pleasant way.

All little boys like to play with balls, our twins just fall for balls. Which little boy does not want to become a football player? The ball is a timeless toy and it always makes the children a lot of fun - no matter if playing with a football, scoring a goal or a large gym ball on which you can swing. In the children's playroom, the boys also liked the cars, toy houses and various toys for swinging.

In the video uses the following songs:

snippet.title: CHILDRENS MUSEUM Pretend Play Family FUN for Kids Indoor Play Area
snippet.description:
CHILDRENS MUSEUM Pretend Play Family FUN for Kids Indoor Play Area with Aubrey and Caleb from Fun and Crazy Kids! Hi Friends, Today my family went to a fun children's museum here in Oklahoma! It had all kinds of fun children's activities and fun pretend play activities!  We Got to play pretend doctor, pretend dentist, pretend play with food and fun size grocery shopping. Caleb loved pushing the little grocery cart around the pretend grocery store. But his favorite part of the Children's museum was the construction area. He played in the sandbox with the trucks and rocks forever! He loves to push the trucks around and fill them up with rocks. He also played pretend mechanic and worked on the cars. It was so cute. 

Aubrey's favorite part of the kids museum was the indoor playground and indoor slide. It was a GIANT slide and kind of scary going down. 

We hope you guys liked this video! Don't forget to subscribe to my channel and give this video a BIG THUMBS UP!! I love playing at the Children's Museum...Don/t YOU!  We had so much fun today together as a family. Let us know in the comments what kind of video you want to see next... and we might just end up picking yours!! XOXO-Fun and Crazy Kids!

snippet.description:
So this time we went back to Stella's indoor playground in Skövde. This playground is not big, but it has some attractions that we haven't seen in other playgrounds. The tall inflatable slide is one example that the kids really like.

Stellas's lekland is based on the same concept as Busfabriken and Leo's lekland.

Indoor playground family fun for kids.

snippet.title: Indoor Playground Family Fun for Kids Part 6 with Spelling | Ball Pits, Slides, Tunnels, Rides
snippet.description:
Sisters Taika and Saima visit an indoor playground with their friend Aisla. You'll see them play in a ball pit, on play structures, in tunnels, and more.  It's a video designed to introduce toddlers to spelling. Although they may not be able to spell the words yet on their own, the video serves to introduce them to the wonderful world of letters and words. The words spelled are slide, explore, jump, and climb.

Subscribe to Toddler World TV: https://www.youtube.com/user/toddlerw...


Written, filmed, and directed by Matthew J. Dorman, PhD
Music by Little Blue Globe Band

Copyright 2017 Toddler World TV
